1. callback function doesn't automatically make code asynchronous. 
2. AJAX calls are probably the most important use-case of Asynchronous JavaScript.
3. 'use-strict' - all the JavaScript variables should have defined data type. 
4. function invocation creates a brand new execution context in the 'code' phase [2 phases : memory allocation & code execution] 
5. 'split()' method converts a string into an array. 
